WEBVTT

00:21.563 --> 00:23.440
[theme music playing]

02:08.503 --> 02:10.588
[Kala] It's still not exactly the same...

02:12.632 --> 02:14.259
but I think it's close enough.

02:14.342 --> 02:15.426
Will it work?

02:15.510 --> 02:19.639
It should, but since I don't understand
exactly what it's doing, I can't be sure.

02:21.141 --> 02:25.061
-I'm just gonna have to test it.
-Oh, not alone. We should do it together.

02:25.145 --> 02:26.271
Hmm...

02:26.354 --> 02:28.940
It would give us more control
if something goes wrong.

02:29.941 --> 02:31.943
I could come to Bombay after London.

02:33.278 --> 02:34.404
How's Will?

02:39.117 --> 02:40.201
Not good.

02:41.452 --> 02:43.913
What happened was awful.

02:45.790 --> 02:47.625
But it isn't his fault.

02:48.626 --> 02:51.212
He shouldn't blame himself
for his father's death.

02:52.922 --> 02:53.840
What's hard for Will

02:53.965 --> 02:57.552
is that all the things
that were broken between them...

02:58.678 --> 03:00.597
they can't ever be fixed.

03:07.020 --> 03:08.479
Can I ask you something?

03:09.355 --> 03:13.401
And if it's inappropriate, please tell me.
I know sometimes I say things I shouldn't.

03:13.484 --> 03:14.694
No, you don't.

03:15.904 --> 03:17.488
I would ask the same thing.

03:20.450 --> 03:23.036
You want to know what it's like
between Will and me.

03:26.915 --> 03:29.959
It's much more intense
than when I visit with any of you.

03:30.793 --> 03:32.128
It's more physical.

03:34.631 --> 03:38.635
I never understood the word "presence"
until we were together.

03:42.263 --> 03:44.807
And if you're wondering about the sex...

03:46.267 --> 03:48.645
no matter what I say, it won't be enough.

03:50.355 --> 03:52.065
Yeah, it's pretty amazing.

03:59.614 --> 04:01.032
And what about now?

04:01.950 --> 04:04.160
What's it like when one of you is in pain?

04:09.249 --> 04:13.127
[Riley] Right now, I can feel his grief.

04:15.421 --> 04:18.549
It's only bearable
because the alternative is not.

04:19.926 --> 04:22.845
["In Need" playing]

04:31.104 --> 04:34.649
♪ No, I can't quite conceive ♪

04:34.732 --> 04:38.361
♪ What all of this means ♪

04:39.696 --> 04:45.576
♪ I might be wrong
But, darling, can't you see? ♪

04:47.078 --> 04:52.834
♪ This bond between us
Seems so special to me ♪

04:54.210 --> 05:00.258
♪ Some kind of clear unspoken chemistry ♪

05:01.050 --> 05:03.720
♪ The message you're sending is mixed ♪

05:04.387 --> 05:07.598
♪ I'm broken, I need to be fixed ♪

05:07.682 --> 05:11.102
♪ I'm in need of attention ♪

05:11.185 --> 05:14.647
♪ I'm in need of love ♪

05:14.731 --> 05:18.484
♪ She's the rope that holds me ♪

05:18.568 --> 05:23.865
♪ Yes, I know she knows me well enough ♪

05:31.581 --> 05:32.915
We need to talk.

05:38.588 --> 05:40.089
You've been hiding?

05:40.882 --> 05:43.885
It's difficult for me
in Berlin right now.

05:44.469 --> 05:46.012
Because of Lila?

05:48.681 --> 05:51.434
I was surprised
you came to the restaurant.

05:52.101 --> 05:54.312
Surprised? Why?

05:57.774 --> 06:00.568
Maybe everything would be easier for you
if I wasn't--

06:00.651 --> 06:03.029
No. No, don't you dare.

06:20.463 --> 06:23.257
I don't know when my life
became so confusing.

06:27.386 --> 06:29.347
I don't know how to fix it.

06:30.932 --> 06:33.601
Because, for me, fixing something

06:33.684 --> 06:35.895
does not mean shooting someone
with a rocket launcher,

06:35.978 --> 06:39.065
to which I would like to point out
that much of your present trouble

06:39.148 --> 06:42.693
is a direct result of this kind
of violent choice,

06:42.777 --> 06:44.403
so the jury is most definitely still out

06:44.487 --> 06:48.533
as to whether that is ever a good solution
to anything, but...

06:48.616 --> 06:49.742
I know...

06:50.910 --> 06:54.997
I know...
that I don't want to hurt Rajan.

07:04.048 --> 07:05.091
But...

07:06.217 --> 07:10.221
I also know that if something
were to happen to you...

07:15.768 --> 07:20.022
if I were no longer able to feel what I...

07:22.525 --> 07:24.110
feel when...

07:42.712 --> 07:45.756
I know my life would no longer
feel worth living.

07:49.010 --> 07:50.428
I will come to Bombay.

07:51.888 --> 07:53.097
You can't.

07:53.723 --> 07:55.516
-What?
-You can't.

07:55.600 --> 07:56.642
Enough.

07:56.726 --> 08:00.855
I've listened to you talk in circles
about what's right and proper,

08:01.355 --> 08:04.400
why you have to do this
or you shouldn't do that.

08:04.817 --> 08:06.777
I don't give a shit about any of it.

08:07.570 --> 08:10.990
I don't care about rules,
about what's right or wrong.

08:11.073 --> 08:13.201
What matters to me is this. Us.

08:14.410 --> 08:15.286
Right now.

08:27.006 --> 08:28.674
And I know you feel the same.

08:32.595 --> 08:33.763
I do.

08:40.436 --> 08:43.105
But I can't be with you in my city.

08:44.232 --> 08:45.691
I'll come to Berlin.

08:46.567 --> 08:47.944
Too dangerous.

08:49.320 --> 08:52.865
Then we'll go somewhere else,
where no one knows us.

08:54.283 --> 08:55.284
When?

08:55.368 --> 08:57.828
I'll talk to Rajan when he comes home.

08:59.705 --> 09:02.124
I have to tell him
what is happening to me.

09:04.669 --> 09:06.337
I owe him the truth.

09:16.097 --> 09:18.891
[Gorski] Will would come over,
we'd do it together.

09:18.975 --> 09:21.060
But Will's not here.
He ain't fucking here.

09:21.143 --> 09:23.354
Should a man in his condition
really be drinking?

09:25.856 --> 09:27.275
I found him on the floor.

09:27.358 --> 09:28.943
[whispers] On the floor?

09:29.026 --> 09:31.237
[Whispers] Will was working
with Jonas Maliki.

09:31.320 --> 09:32.530
[Will] They're lies! They're lies.

09:32.613 --> 09:34.991
No one believed me. Not even my dad.

09:35.074 --> 09:37.159
You're actually out of your fucking mind.

09:37.243 --> 09:38.661
Dad, you've gotta believe me.

09:39.453 --> 09:42.623
Will, help me. Will, please.

09:45.751 --> 09:47.253
-Help me.
-[sobbing]

09:47.336 --> 09:49.714
-It's about Sara, Dad.
-Oh, no.

09:49.797 --> 09:52.133
-[sobbing]
-I know.

09:52.717 --> 09:55.845
You want to run as far from the pain
as you can.

09:57.179 --> 10:00.349
Dad! Come back!

10:00.433 --> 10:05.354
I know, baby. I went so far,
I didn't know how to get back.

10:05.938 --> 10:07.481
[Whispers] Terrible news.

10:07.565 --> 10:08.899
[gasps]

10:09.442 --> 10:12.737
How sad to let your father die alone
like that.

10:12.820 --> 10:14.780
[sobbing] Just stay the fuck away from me.

10:15.698 --> 10:16.949
Or what?

10:17.950 --> 10:20.870
I know things were difficult
between you and your father.

10:21.537 --> 10:26.459
Maybe... Maybe you didn't go
to your father because, in the end,

10:27.043 --> 10:28.878
he wasn't that important to you.

10:30.379 --> 10:32.632
Maybe you're not the son
you thought you were.

10:34.050 --> 10:38.262
I can imagine facing that truth
would be particularly painful.

10:41.098 --> 10:42.933
[snorts, grunts]

10:45.561 --> 10:51.150
You and I?
We are getting closer and closer, Will.

11:31.482 --> 11:33.943
[Spanish hip-hop playing]

11:59.385 --> 12:00.970
Mr. Wrangler will see you now.

12:02.263 --> 12:03.097
Okay.

12:03.180 --> 12:07.768
Mr. Bak wants everything to be perfect.

12:09.812 --> 12:14.733
You are the face of his hospitality.

12:23.868 --> 12:26.162
There will be a lot of foreign guests...

12:27.246 --> 12:31.625
so you have to be ready
for a variety of tastes.

12:37.381 --> 12:38.507
Make me a Sidecar.

12:50.895 --> 12:52.521
Look, Lito, here's the thing.

12:52.605 --> 12:54.398
I'm old-school.

12:54.482 --> 12:57.234
Box office bores me.
That crap is for accountants.

12:57.318 --> 13:00.905
I care about one thing and one thing only.

13:01.864 --> 13:04.658
You touch me here, I'm yours.

13:05.701 --> 13:09.663
You don't,
I don't care how many fans you have,

13:09.747 --> 13:12.625
