17:22.291 --> 17:24.793
[speaking Swahili]

17:24.877 --> 17:26.837
[in English]
End of the line! End of the line!

17:26.920 --> 17:28.714
Don't forget, rally this weekend!

17:28.797 --> 17:30.883
It's gonna be off the chain! Rally.

17:30.966 --> 17:34.678
This weekend. Off... the... chain!

17:35.387 --> 17:37.931
Rally around. This weekend. Off the chain!

17:39.808 --> 17:42.978
[upbeat electronic music playing]

18:10.464 --> 18:11.882
[exhales]

18:20.390 --> 18:21.433
Thank you.

18:34.071 --> 18:36.156
-[squealing]
-Cool it. Cool it down.

18:36.240 --> 18:37.199
-At the bar.
-Who?

18:37.783 --> 18:40.619
How is it possible that our lives
are intersecting with people

18:40.702 --> 18:43.330
that I have read about in the line
at the grocery store?

18:43.413 --> 18:47.126
Oh, there he is! There's our Jordi!

18:47.876 --> 18:50.337
-Oh...
-Mr. Wrangler.

18:50.420 --> 18:52.381
-Oh...
-Thank you for inviting us.

18:52.464 --> 18:55.008
Kit. Please.
We're still in the honeymoon stage.

18:55.092 --> 18:57.594
-And you remember Carmen.
-Hello, Carmen.

18:58.637 --> 19:01.515
-That's real, isn't it?
-Oh...

19:02.683 --> 19:05.102
Oh, this old thing?

19:05.561 --> 19:06.812
Twenty-four karat, hon.

19:06.895 --> 19:09.815
And because everyone wants to know...

19:10.315 --> 19:11.608
hell, yes, I did.

19:12.151 --> 19:13.277
The minute I got home,

19:13.360 --> 19:17.156
