27:19.095 --> 27:25.810
♪ Strayed above the highway aisle ♪

27:34.486 --> 27:37.238
Hey. Where'd you go?

27:39.532 --> 27:41.117
I had to get out of there.

27:42.952 --> 27:44.579
I couldn't breathe.

27:49.209 --> 27:50.293
I know.

27:53.838 --> 27:56.800
There's nothing more frightening
than having a dream come true.

28:07.352 --> 28:09.187
How is it I can feel like...

28:11.189 --> 28:14.359
everything in my life
has been leading me to this beach,

28:14.442 --> 28:18.863
and at the same time feel like...
I don't belong here at all?

28:20.782 --> 28:22.784
Yeah, I've felt that way myself.

28:24.744 --> 28:26.663
I think many people have.

28:29.249 --> 28:33.670
When that happens to me, it is usually
because there's something I'm afraid of.

28:38.341 --> 28:40.760
What if I do this movie
and everyone finds out?

28:43.388 --> 28:44.723
What?

28:46.057 --> 28:47.308
That I'm a fraud.

28:49.227 --> 28:50.854
That I'm not a good actor.

28:51.771 --> 28:54.607
No, no, no, no.
Baby, baby, baby, baby, look at me.

28:57.360 --> 28:59.529
You are a great actor.

29:01.156 --> 29:07.162
And you're scared right now because art,
like life, is... is full of risk.

29:07.245 --> 29:08.997
And that's beautiful.

29:19.924 --> 29:21.634
But I will remind you...

29:23.261 --> 29:26.931
what you said to me when we were
watching From Here to Eternity.

29:28.808 --> 29:31.144
That this wasn't a career
you were chasing.

29:33.438 --> 29:34.522
It was a dream.

29:42.614 --> 29:44.115
So tell me, my love...

29:46.034 --> 29:49.704
if your dream isn't worth the risk,
what is?

29:49.788 --> 29:53.750
♪ Now to know it in my memory ♪

29:53.833 --> 29:57.128
-[Lito] Wait!
-[Hernando laughs]

29:57.712 --> 30:00.548
[whooping]

30:03.176 --> 30:05.845
-[whooping]
-[laughing]

30:11.601 --> 30:17.816
♪ High above the highway aisle ♪

30:26.241 --> 30:32.038
♪ Jagged vacance, thick with ice ♪

30:36.459 --> 30:40.338
♪ I could see for miles, miles, miles ♪

30:42.006 --> 30:44.926
From queer to eternity!

30:46.845 --> 30:50.181
[cheering]

31:03.778 --> 31:05.488
These people are here for me?

31:05.572 --> 31:06.823
Yes, they are.

31:09.576 --> 31:11.786
-But do they know I'm just--
-Just like them?

31:12.912 --> 31:14.038
They do.

31:16.207 --> 31:18.960
[cheering]

31:24.048 --> 31:26.551
-You'll be fine, son.
-How do you know that?

31:27.427 --> 31:28.595
Because your whole life,

31:28.678 --> 31:31.222
every really good day,
and every truly bad one,

31:31.306 --> 31:33.516
has been preparing you for this moment.

31:34.350 --> 31:35.435
[man over microphone] For too long...

31:37.395 --> 31:39.230
we have elected promises.

31:39.314 --> 31:40.940
-[crowd cheering]
-[speaking Swahili]

31:41.024 --> 31:44.819
For too long, we have elected liars.

31:44.903 --> 31:46.321
[cheering]

31:46.404 --> 31:47.864
And hypocrites.

31:49.324 --> 31:51.367
We have elected thieves.

31:53.036 --> 31:56.664
The time has come to elect a real man.

31:56.748 --> 32:01.377
I give you,
from the Kenya Democratic Reform Party...

32:02.545 --> 32:07.800
Capheus "Van Damn" Onyango!

32:07.884 --> 32:11.179
[cheering]

32:48.967 --> 32:50.426
Just drive the bus.

32:52.762 --> 32:55.139
[cheering continues]

33:36.889 --> 33:37.974
[Capheus] Hello.

33:48.985 --> 33:50.570
[crowd silences]

33:52.572 --> 33:54.615
I thought if you were going
to vote for me...

33:57.076 --> 33:58.911
you should know a few things about me.

34:02.832 --> 34:04.125
Once, a Kikuyu woman...

34:05.501 --> 34:07.503
and a Luo man
fell in love with each other.

34:09.547 --> 34:11.507
They were urged by both of their families

34:11.591 --> 34:14.552
not to marry outside the tribal boundary,
but...

34:16.637 --> 34:22.226
love is a bridge and not a wall,
if we let it be.

34:24.020 --> 34:25.730
They became husband and wife.

34:27.356 --> 34:30.068
At first, they lived
with my father's family in Ahero,

34:30.151 --> 34:34.530
but I'm afraid the Luo village found
a hundred ways to make the new bride

34:34.614 --> 34:36.240
feel as if she was a trespasser.

34:36.991 --> 34:38.826
So, when I was only a few months old,

34:39.535 --> 34:42.205
my parents went to live in the village
that my mother was born.

34:43.081 --> 34:46.334
Now it was my father's turn to be made
to feel like he was an outsider

34:46.417 --> 34:47.335
who did not belong.

34:48.044 --> 34:50.129
My parents had to leave their homes...

34:51.297 --> 34:53.132
to find a city where no one knew them.

34:54.759 --> 34:56.969
The same prejudice that drove them away...

34:58.596 --> 35:01.140
was also responsible
for taking my father's life

35:01.224 --> 35:03.726
when a political difference
became a tribal war.

35:10.274 --> 35:13.611
I share this story because
you have heard many rumors about me...

35:15.822 --> 35:18.574
and I felt it was time
to explain who and what I am.

35:21.994 --> 35:23.496
I am Kikuyu.

35:23.579 --> 35:26.040
[cheering]

35:29.794 --> 35:30.962
I'm Luo.

35:31.462 --> 35:33.673
[cheering]

35:35.591 --> 35:38.010
My business partner and best friend
is also mixed.

35:39.262 --> 35:40.555
His father, Sudanese.

35:41.556 --> 35:42.849
His mother, Kenyan.

35:42.932 --> 35:44.851
[cheering]

35:45.476 --> 35:48.146
These are facts that he and I
have never talked about,

35:48.646 --> 35:50.148
because for us...

35:51.482 --> 35:52.775
they have never mattered.

35:56.654 --> 36:00.366
Nothing good ever happens when people
care more about our differences...

36:01.617 --> 36:02.994
than the things we share in common.

36:03.828 --> 36:05.788
The future I hope for
is the same as yours.

36:07.999 --> 36:13.045
A future where our children grow up
never knowing love as a wall...

36:16.632 --> 36:18.301
but only as a bridge.

36:18.384 --> 36:21.137
[cheering]

36:26.225 --> 36:29.395
[indistinct shouting]

36:35.359 --> 36:36.319
Please. Please.

36:38.487 --> 36:40.656
Please. Please, no violence. Please.

36:44.744 --> 36:47.455
No! Please, stop! Please!

36:48.873 --> 36:50.750
-Don't do this, please!
-[screaming]

36:52.960 --> 36:54.086
Don't do this!

36:56.631 --> 36:58.257
We have to get you out of here!

36:59.842 --> 37:02.053
Wait! What about my family?

37:02.136 --> 37:04.805
Your family is safer without you.
Come on, let's go!

37:10.853 --> 37:14.523
[crowd shouting in distance]

37:37.964 --> 37:40.967
[crowd shouting]

38:02.405 --> 38:03.906
[distorted] Capheus!

38:06.784 --> 38:08.119
[distorted] What?

38:10.329 --> 38:12.665
[distorted] It's a trap!

38:14.875 --> 38:16.168
He's got a knife!

38:49.869 --> 38:52.330
[crowd continues shouting]

39:58.437 --> 40:00.898
[Will sobbing]

40:20.376 --> 40:21.377
[Riley] Will.

40:25.506 --> 40:26.715
Will.

40:33.264 --> 40:34.682
Will...

40:35.850 --> 40:37.351
that was not good.

40:40.271 --> 40:42.148
I know you're in pain.

40:43.691 --> 40:46.152
I know you feel lost, but...

40:47.778 --> 40:49.321
right now, we need you.

40:51.991 --> 40:53.242
I need you.

40:56.328 --> 40:57.997
Capheus needs you.

41:05.004 --> 41:06.380
I'm sorry.

41:08.841 --> 41:10.342
When my father was killed....

41:12.970 --> 41:14.597
I went a bit crazy, too.

41:26.358 --> 41:27.860
No, I...

41:30.070 --> 41:31.405
I fucked up.

41:37.828 --> 41:39.371
And it won't happen again.

41:42.750 --> 41:44.126
And don't worry.

41:44.877 --> 41:46.337
He's not gonna hurt you.

41:48.506 --> 41:49.590
How do you know that?

41:51.592 --> 41:52.885
The safety's on.

41:53.886 --> 41:55.262
So it is.

41:55.346 --> 41:58.015
[laughs] Ah!

42:01.435 --> 42:02.811
Why did you save me?

42:04.563 --> 42:07.316
The last scene of
The Legend of Superpower and Van Damn

42:07.399 --> 42:10.736
sure as shit don't belong
to some political bullshit plot

42:10.819 --> 42:12.321
cooked up by bossman Mandiba.

42:13.822 --> 42:14.823
But you work for him.

42:16.200 --> 42:18.869
Mandiba aren't from Kibera
like you and me.

42:19.954 --> 42:23.624
See, the thing he don't understand
about us mad fucking slumdogs...

42:24.124 --> 42:28.504
you try to put a leash on us,
we'll rip your hands off at the wrist.

42:33.968 --> 42:39.598
Meaning, I've got plans, Van Damn.
Big plans.

42:44.979 --> 42:47.189
Now get the fuck out of my new car.

42:56.490 --> 42:58.867
Capheus! Ohh!

42:58.951 --> 43:00.744
It's okay, Mama. It's okay.

43:01.620 --> 43:04.290
-Oh, I was so scared.
-It's okay. I'm okay.

43:04.999 --> 43:05.833
Ow!

43:05.916 --> 43:08.877
Oh, my God. What happened?

43:08.961 --> 43:10.129
I'm okay. I'm okay.

43:16.385 --> 43:20.681
What you said on that stage
was good for people to hear.

43:22.057 --> 43:24.101
You were amazing.

43:25.894 --> 43:28.188
I want to grow up so I can vote for you.

43:28.272 --> 43:29.732
[laughter]

43:29.815 --> 43:31.275
After what happened...

43:33.193 --> 43:35.112
I don't think anyone's
going to vote for me.

43:36.280 --> 43:39.617
I wouldn't be so sure, Capheus.
People heard you out there.

43:39.700 --> 43:43.329
And they know the violence was caused
by Mandiba's men.

43:43.412 --> 43:47.875
He's right. Before those demonstrators,
you could feel the excitement.

43:47.958 --> 43:51.211
-It was more than just excitement.
-They loved what you said.

43:51.295 --> 43:53.797
They did. And I did, too.

43:53.881 --> 43:56.967
I think everyone at the park
felt the exact same thing.

43:57.051 --> 43:59.595
That there was a chance,
maybe even a last chance,

43:59.678 --> 44:02.097
for a future that doesn't look
exactly like our past.

44:02.890 --> 44:04.933
Yeah. That's true.

44:55.025 --> 44:56.485
Tonight's the gala.

45:01.949 --> 45:03.867
Will you try to stop me?

45:04.701 --> 45:06.370
Do you want me to stop you?

45:12.459 --> 45:15.421
Every cop knows there are times
where the only choice you have left...

45:16.672 --> 45:18.298
is to defend yourself.

46:16.315 --> 46:17.691
I missed my cop.

46:19.443 --> 46:20.777
He missed you.

46:36.376 --> 46:37.628
Welcome home.

47:35.352 --> 47:37.479
[applause]

48:07.676 --> 48:09.678
The security is very perimeter-based.

48:11.430 --> 48:13.098
If Sun's right,
he gives some kind of address,

48:13.181 --> 48:14.516
we should make our move just after that.

48:16.059 --> 48:17.978
How do we get him out of the building?

48:18.604 --> 48:20.314
Looks like the garage
is our only viable exit.

48:20.397 --> 48:21.356
Got it.

48:21.440 --> 48:24.443
-[Nomi] We need building schematics.
-[Bug] On it.

48:24.526 --> 48:26.987
-And then?
-We get him to tell the truth.

48:27.571 --> 48:29.823
A coerced confession
isn't admissible evidence.

48:29.906 --> 48:31.116
We trick him.

48:31.867 --> 48:33.869
What if we can't get him
out of the building?

48:35.912 --> 48:38.624
He'll keep coming after her,
because as long as she's alive,

48:38.707 --> 48:39.958
someone will know what he has done.

48:40.834 --> 48:41.752
One way or another...

48:44.463 --> 48:45.464
we end it.

48:52.220 --> 48:54.473
We take everything that matters...

48:55.932 --> 48:57.643
we push all of it into this...

49:06.151 --> 49:07.569
and we fight for it.
